NT||cp|8|AT|^B@2^Z@3^*Bhondo717: ^*N|cp||at|Anna you are correct. Let's look at what is going on. Assume Stan has 12 or 13 HCP and Anna has 19. That leaves 9 or 10 between Dorothy and I. Given no additional information, Anna can guess they are split evenly, giving me 4 or 5 points. So, it is likely we are close to making game. Additionally, Anna is well placed behind the opening bidder. Her high cards are more likely to win tricks because Stan is more likely to have the missing high cards. For both those reasons a) our side should be close to having enough HCP to make game and b) Anna's HCP are well placed as well as c) we have a 9 card it. 4H is a very good bid.|
