NT||cp|8|AT|^B@2^Z@3^*Bhondo717: ^*N|cp||at|Now, let's discuss the opening lead. Stan does not have a good lead. A singleton trump often gives away a trick and should be avoided. It is rarely right to lead an unprotected Ace as I have said many times. So, clubs are out. That leaves spades, and leading away from the King-Jack is not appetizing either. I would have led a spade myself (the SJ is the Standard lead) and that actually works well on this hand, as Dorothy scores 2 ruffs.|
