cp|8|AT|^B@2^Z@3^*Bhondo717: ^*N|cp||at|Let us look at the bidding first. Although sometimes you open 2N with an off shape hand, to show your values, generally you should not if you have better alternatives. The two reasons are, a) with a singleton partner may put you in the wrong contract, and b) you might miss a suit slam. As it turns out, 6C has plays although it is hard to bid and play. I would open 1C with Marge's hand, and then jump shift to 2S. That describes her shape and points very well.|
