cp|8|AT|^B@2^Z@3^*Bhondo717:^*N|cp||at| Okay, discussing the bidding is first. Some of you may remember that on this auction, Marty recommends the "OBAR" approach. OBAR stands for "Opponents Bid and Raise" which is exactly what this auction was. He believes, and I agree, that if it goes 1x-p-2x, you can "pre-balance" if you have something to say. I am not sure Ann's hearts are worthy of bidding but, if she had the same number of points and a sixth heart, they would be. Some people would say that Ann can "double" to show the other 2 suits. That is known as a "responsive double" and if you play those, Ann has a good responsive double, although she does have an extra heart.|
