NT||cp|8|AT|^B@2^Z@3^*Bhondo717: ^*N|cp||at|As to the play, there is one good point here. I am sure you noticed I ducked the first spade. That was a very important play. Because, if the opponents start trump and take my trumps off the board, I still have spades controlled. And if they don't play trump, I still have time to ruff my losing spade as I did. As it turns out, if Ginny plays 2 rounds of trump, I end up making 4 or 5. The heart lead was better. However, the key play was ducking the first spade.|
